The paper deals with designing codes for communication over a channel, which is a typical topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on networks, which suggests the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also deals with coordination, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). The use of polar codes for channel resolvability suggests the sub-category of coding theory and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper provides a low complexity solution, which suggests the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
